In summary, the following elements are available for the representation of the outermost structure of a TEI document:
As noted above, the teiHeader element is formally declared in the header module (see chapter ). The TEI and teiCorpus elements are formally declared as follows:
&TEI; &teiCorpus;

Each of these elements is further described in the following subsections. The elements text, body, group, and floatingText are formally declared as follows:
&text; &body; &group; &floatingText;
Elements front and back are declared separately, and are further discussed in sections and . The group and floatingText elements, used for more complex or composite text structures, are further discussed in section . Other textual elements, such as paragraphs, lists or phrases, which nest within these major structural elements, are discussed in chapter , in the case of elements which can appear in any kind of document, or elsewhere in the case of elements specific to particular kinds of document.

Formal definitions for these elements are as follows:


&div1;
&div2;
&div3;
&div4;
&div5;
&div6;
&div7;

The elements discussed in this section are formally defined as
follows:


&trailer;
&byline;
&dateline;
&argument;
&epigraph;
&opener;
&closer;
&salute;
&signed;

Those elements in the above list which are not defined elsewhere have
the following formal declarations:


&titlePage;
&docTitle;
&titlePart;
&docAuthor;
&imprimatur;
&docEdition;
&docImprint;
&docDate;

The back element; since there are no other specialized
back-matter tags, nothing else is defined here.

&back;
